    {
      "key": "117b6be0-5df6-44fc-a0f8-3dab6ff1f612",
      "position": 1,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-desktop\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Transition:** Direct students to Lesson 6, Level 1. Give them time to discover how it works, run across the scenarios that pop up as they are playing the game, and attempt to troubleshoot them.",
        "duration": "20",
        "name": "Troubleshooting",
        "progression_name": "Troubleshooting",
        "tips": [
          {
            "type": "teachingTip",
            "markdown": "Remind students that they can’t break this level so encourage them to try as many things with the level as they can think of to solve the problems they encounter."
          }
        ]
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "117b6be0-5df6-44fc-a0f8-3dab6ff1f612",
        "lesson_activity.key": "2fb2e33e-2059-4da7-a118-e5f682bc10fb"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "1a4fc5cd-048c-4fbc-b533-bddbabb2f371",
      "position": 2,
      "properties": {
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "1a4fc5cd-048c-4fbc-b533-bddbabb2f371",
        "lesson_activity.key": "2fb2e33e-2059-4da7-a118-e5f682bc10fb"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "609620e9-bdc5-496a-8f42-bcef2dbfb430",
      "position": 3,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Direct students to Lesson 5, Level 2 and have them answer the prompts.",
        "progression_name": "Reflection",
        "tips": [
          {
            "type": "teachingTip",
            "markdown": "This level is designed to use the Student Summaries feature, which lets you view and display the responses from the class. This requires having this level opened on your computer and, in the teacher panel, selecting the current section of your classes. [**Click here to learn more about viewing student responses**](https://support.code.org/hc/en-us/articles/14544890300301-Can-I-see-a-summary-of-all-my-students-responses-for-question-based-levels). If you are unable to use the student summaries, you can also run this as an unplugged discussion where students vote in their seats or move to different corners of the room depending on their responses."
          }
        ]
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "609620e9-bdc5-496a-8f42-bcef2dbfb430",
        "lesson_activity.key": "2fb2e33e-2059-4da7-a118-e5f682bc10fb"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "a245549d-ef32-4d62-b1de-4026731a5531",
      "position": 4,
      "properties": {
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "a245549d-ef32-4d62-b1de-4026731a5531",
        "lesson_activity.key": "2fb2e33e-2059-4da7-a118-e5f682bc10fb"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "c4deab5e-2eae-43a6-a2d9-2c519e015ece",
      "position": 5,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-comments\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Discuss:** *Which scenario felt most realistic?*\n- Use the information from the student summary screen (or other class voting method) to guide the conversation. Invite a student from each area to share their rationale.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-lightbulb-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Discussion Goal:** Listen for students to share comparisons to real-world troubleshooting situations they’ve encountered and how those were similar or different to what they encountered in the simulation. Pull out the idea of a process being followed no matter what the problem you are facing.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-comments\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Discuss:** *What is one step you would always try first in a real-world troubleshooting process?*\n- Use the information from the student summary screen (or other class voting method) to guide the conversation. Pick out themes or specific answers for students to expand on.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-lightbulb-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Discussion Goal:** Listen for students to share the “why” behind the step they picked and have them expand on their reasoning. Some examples of things students might share:\n- “I always restart my device when there is an issue because I’ve found that it fixes most problems even if I don’t necessarily understand why.”\n- “I start by googling the error or problem I’m facing to see if I can find a youtube video showing how to fix it. That way I have a step-by-step guide that I can go through at my own pace.”\n- “I would try anything that would help me narrow down the what it causing the issue because that’s what we learned a few lessons ago.”"
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "c4deab5e-2eae-43a6-a2d9-2c519e015ece",
        "lesson_activity.key": "2fb2e33e-2059-4da7-a118-e5f682bc10fb"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "6b1a3131-9cd5-4e9c-b11d-53261ce748ec",
      "position": 6,
      "properties": {
        "description": "Now that we’ve worked on troubleshooting when things aren’t working correctly, we are going to focus on solving a different type of problem: how do you make sure your computer system performs at its best for the task you are trying to accomplish? This is known as optimization.",
        "duration": "15",
        "name": "Optimizing",
        "remarks": true
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "6b1a3131-9cd5-4e9c-b11d-53261ce748ec",
        "lesson_activity.key": "2fb2e33e-2059-4da7-a118-e5f682bc10fb"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "bb84d681-fc09-42d6-b0e1-7dd501e7288d",
      "position": 7,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Explain the difference between troubleshooting and optimization.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:**  Place students in pairs.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-file-text-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Distribute:** Give each pair of students a copy of the Optimization activity guide.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-desktop\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Transition:**  Direct students to Lesson 6, Level 3. Students complete the activity guide with the chatbot.",
        "progression_name": "Optimization"
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "bb84d681-fc09-42d6-b0e1-7dd501e7288d",
        "lesson_activity.key": "2fb2e33e-2059-4da7-a118-e5f682bc10fb"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "a1e61a99-7045-456e-bc62-9151a50b40e9",
      "position": 8,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-refresh\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Circulate:** Look for students going back and forth between discussing the options amongst themselves and asking the AI Chat for input. If students aren’t engaging with each other, use questioning to get them to explain their process and thinking about whichever scenario they are working through.",
        "tips": [
          {
            "type": "assessmentOpportunity",
            "markdown": "You may choose to collect the Activity Guide to see how students grasped the concept of Optimization."
          }
        ]
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "a1e61a99-7045-456e-bc62-9151a50b40e9",
        "lesson_activity.key": "2fb2e33e-2059-4da7-a118-e5f682bc10fb"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "b31db3d4-1d44-435f-8219-8cac1689f551",
      "position": 9,
      "properties": {
        "progression_name": "Student Survey"
      },
