        "activity_section.key": "b31db3d4-1d44-435f-8219-8cac1689f551",
        "lesson_activity.key": "2fb2e33e-2059-4da7-a118-e5f682bc10fb"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "91bc4ab2-c2fb-45f2-85f2-936fd28261bb",
      "position": 1,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Review the lesson objectives.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Review the Question of the Day.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Direct students to the end of the Unit Guide for Lesson 5. Have students reflect on the lesson using Closing the Loop.",
        "tips": [
          {
            "type": "assessmentOpportunity",
            "markdown": "The Unit Guides can be collected at the end of the day if you’d like to use the answers to these prompts to gauge how well students grasped the concepts around troubleshooting and optimization and which might need further review."
          }
        ]
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "91bc4ab2-c2fb-45f2-85f2-936fd28261bb",
        "lesson_activity.key": "0dfb56cb-e7ae-4854-a62e-aa625e25fcfd"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "4d8c6ffd-f5ee-4b97-b871-7531191f26f8",
      "position": 1,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Place students into groups of 4.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Give each student a blank piece of paper.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Have students write \"Input\", \"Output\", \"Storage\", and \"Internal Components\" on separate pieces of paper.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Students participate in a round-robin activity where they brainstorm an idea quickly, and pass their paper to the left. They start by writing one hardware example under the category heading on their paper and circle their example on the paper. They then pass their paper to the left and repeat this process, adding as many examples as possible in the time given. If a student cannot think of an example, they can skip and pass the paper.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-refresh\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Circulate:** As the students work, encourage them to keep coming up with examples. If a group appears stuck, encourage them to switch papers. The time will go fast, and the idea is to brainstorm as quickly as possible.\n\n\n",
        "tips": [
          {
            "type": "teachingTip",
            "markdown": "This activity should be fun and fast-paced. Encourage students to write what is on their mind, even if it might not be 100% correct. They can revise and refine their contributions between rounds. There is a teacher resource available with a list of hardware suggestions to assist as needed."
          }
        ]
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "4d8c6ffd-f5ee-4b97-b871-7531191f26f8",
        "lesson_activity.key": "4b53bd0e-7b76-49a2-97bf-cd455215fb68"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "16f78642-a24e-47a7-b4c5-2bcfc0418490",
      "position": 2,
      "properties": {
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "16f78642-a24e-47a7-b4c5-2bcfc0418490",
        "lesson_activity.key": "4b53bd0e-7b76-49a2-97bf-cd455215fb68"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "918930ad-98be-494a-9858-741c16d5d75d",
      "position": 3,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-comments\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Discuss:** *Could you make a working computer from all of the hardware that your group has listed, or are there important components missing?*\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-lightbulb-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Discussion Goal:** Students collaboratively analyze the list of computer hardware components generated during the activity to determine if they have all the essential parts needed to build a functioning computer. They identify any missing components and explain why each component is critical to the computer's operation. This discussion aims to deepen their understanding of computer architecture and enhance their critical thinking and communication skills.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Have students redistribute the papers. Students choose one of the components on the paper from Round One and write a definition, description, analogy, or make a fast sketch that explains what this component is or what it does within a computer system. They then pass papers to the left and repeat the process.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-refresh\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Circulate:** As the students work, encourage them to keep coming up with contributions. If a group member appears stuck, encourage them to switch papers.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-comments\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Discuss:** *What is the importance of this hardware component in a computer system? Are there descriptions, analogies, or images you might add to further explain the component?*\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-lightbulb-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Discussion Goal:** This discussion seeks to help them recall prior learning and discuss the work that they have created as a group.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Introduce the learning objectives.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Introduce the Question of the Day."
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "918930ad-98be-494a-9858-741c16d5d75d",
        "lesson_activity.key": "4b53bd0e-7b76-49a2-97bf-cd455215fb68"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "cb48d2b2-5f4f-402d-a52c-327d12163591",
      "position": 1,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Define *build*.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-desktop\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Transition:** Direct students to Lesson 7, Level 1. Students should spend a few minutes exploring PCPartPicker by clicking the blue buttons to explore different components, using the filtering options available on the left-hand side of the screen, or even exploring builds that other users have shared. ",
        "progression_name": "PCPartPicker"
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "cb48d2b2-5f4f-402d-a52c-327d12163591",
        "lesson_activity.key": "a9220a21-94f4-4860-b65c-2ff45acc28d6"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "09d203f9-8ddc-46f8-a8b9-311b11cb35e9",
      "position": 2,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-refresh\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Circulate:** Show students how to click the buttons and search components. Point out the different ways to filter - price, manufacturer, specifications, etc.",
        "tips": [
          {
            "type": "teachingTip",
            "markdown": "[**PCPartPicker.com**](http://pcpartpicker.com/) is a great resource to choose components, add them in a visual UI, and to check for compatibility issues. If this website is unavailable, there are also plenty of guides on sample builds that are available online. Here are some examples:\n\n- [**Best PC builds for gaming 2025**](https://www.tomshardware.com/best-picks/best-pc-builds-gaming) from Tom's Hardware\n\n- [**Want a Better PC? Try Building Your Own**](https://www.wired.com/story/how-to-build-a-pc/) by Wired\n\n- [**How to Build a PC: The Ultimate Beginner's Guide**](https://www.pcmag.com/how-to/how-to-build-a-pc-the-ultimate-beginners-guide) by PCMag\n\n- [**The TBG DIY PC Build Guides**](https://techbuyersguru.com/tbg-diy-pc-build-guides/) by the Tech Buyer's Guru"
          }
        ]
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "09d203f9-8ddc-46f8-a8b9-311b11cb35e9",
        "lesson_activity.key": "a9220a21-94f4-4860-b65c-2ff45acc28d6"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "72d33ef3-d40c-415d-bb63-28626db7bc26",
      "position": 3,
      "properties": {
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "72d33ef3-d40c-415d-bb63-28626db7bc26",
        "lesson_activity.key": "a9220a21-94f4-4860-b65c-2ff45acc28d6"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "d8844c08-6f71-4ff2-b166-d50512058ba5",
      "position": 4,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-comments\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Discuss:** *What did you notice about this website? What do you wonder about this website?*\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-lightbulb-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Discussion Goal:** Students might notice that this website helps users build a computer by allowing them to choose a list of compatible parts; it shows prices for different components which makes it easier to budget; there is a section for completed builds that users have shared; and there are warnings that pop up if incompatible parts are selected. Students might wonder: *What are all of the specifications for? What is the difference between brands and manufacturers? Why are some parts more expensive than others?*\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This**: Place students into pairs.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-file-text-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Distribute:** Give each pair a copy of the Build a Computer System activity guide.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-desktop\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Transition:** Direct students to Lesson 6, Level 2. Students should select a user that they want to design a computer system for and complete the User Profile section of the activity guide.",
        "progression_name": "Computer Build User Profiles"
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "d8844c08-6f71-4ff2-b166-d50512058ba5",
        "lesson_activity.key": "a9220a21-94f4-4860-b65c-2ff45acc28d6"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "af6f685a-a64f-4234-b02a-67f42b5c0343",
      "position": 5,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Direct students to Lesson 6, Level 3. Students should complete their activity guide using the PCPartPicker website and the Computer Build Assistant.",
        "progression_name": "Computer Build Assistant"
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "af6f685a-a64f-4234-b02a-67f42b5c0343",
        "lesson_activity.key": "a9220a21-94f4-4860-b65c-2ff45acc28d6"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "0677bb42-37bf-4fb2-98ee-cde98bd229c3",
      "position": 6,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-refresh\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Circulate:** Assist students who are stuck, help craft questions for the AI chatbot with students, ask leading questions to get them to consider the needs of their chosen user.",
        "tips": [
          {
            "type": "assessmentOpportunity",
            "markdown": "The Build a Computer System activity guide can be used to check students' ability to justify computer system design decisions."
          }
        ]
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "0677bb42-37bf-4fb2-98ee-cde98bd229c3",
        "lesson_activity.key": "a9220a21-94f4-4860-b65c-2ff45acc28d6"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "cb4da0fd-0823-44ab-8dea-8e3464365ee8",
      "position": 7,
      "properties": {
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "cb4da0fd-0823-44ab-8dea-8e3464365ee8",
        "lesson_activity.key": "a9220a21-94f4-4860-b65c-2ff45acc28d6"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "06651152-74a3-4661-a705-a084ab60bea9",
      "position": 8,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-comments\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Discuss:** *What is one decision that you had to make in your build to align with your user's needs or preferences?*\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-lightbulb-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Discussion Goal:** Students share how they considered and prioritized needs and preferences while working on their build."
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "06651152-74a3-4661-a705-a084ab60bea9",
        "lesson_activity.key": "a9220a21-94f4-4860-b65c-2ff45acc28d6"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "964b9b2d-ec08-42d4-bfb9-9017a88fb0fb",
      "position": 9,
      "properties": {
        "progression_name": "Student Survey"
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "964b9b2d-ec08-42d4-bfb9-9017a88fb0fb",
        "lesson_activity.key": "a9220a21-94f4-4860-b65c-2ff45acc28d6"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "050029b5-3282-40b9-92c3-b6fda10628c4",
      "position": 1,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Review the learning objectives.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Review the Question of the Day.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-desktop\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Transition:** Direct students to Lesson 6, Level 4. Students should write a news headline that summarizes something important that they learned or a key takeaway from their experience creating their computer build.\n",
        "progression_name": "Check for Understanding",
        "tips": [
          {
            "type": "assessmentOpportunity",
            "markdown": "The News Headline Check for Understanding can be used to assess students' ability to explain the roles of hardware, software, and operating systems in executing tasks."
          }
        ]
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "050029b5-3282-40b9-92c3-b6fda10628c4",
        "lesson_activity.key": "23eca6d4-4b61-46fb-a3ef-711c13b7f32b"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "c475ed09-bee8-44ce-9c44-df8b0b887410",
      "position": 1,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Define *data*.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:**  Place students in pairs.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-file-text-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Distribute:** Give each pair of students a blank piece of paper.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:**  Play the video clip. Students should list the data or types of data that could be collected in this scenario.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-refresh\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Circulate:** Encourage students to think about different types of data that might be collected from the scene: \n- Visual Data - number of vehicles or pedestrians on the street\n- Audio Data - noise level, types of sounds (car horns, rain, footsteps, etc.)\n- Location Data - GPS coordinates of where the video was recorded\n- Environmental Data - Temperature, rain intensity\n- Text Data - Street signs, billboards, shop names, or license plate numbers.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:**  Students repeat the activity again for a different scene. They should write down as many ideas for how data might be gathered from the scenario that they can within a minute.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-refresh\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Circulate:** Encourage students to think about different types of data that might be collected from the scene: \n- Visual Data - Actions being performed (chopping, stirring, plating)\n- Audio Data - Type of sounds (alarms for timers, equipment hums, verbal orders)\n- Location Data - Movements of staff (areas of the kitchen frequently occupied, paths taken between stations)\n- Environmental Data - Kitchen temperature\n- Biometric Data - Stress indicators (heart rate, hurried movements)\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:**  Students repeat the activity again for a different 10 second scene. They should write down as many ideas for how data might be gathered from the scenario that they can within a minute.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-refresh\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Circulate:** Encourage students to think about different types of data that might be collected from the scene: \n- Visual Data - Number and types of trees, plants, or rocks visible\n- Audio Data - Birdsong frequency and species identification\n- Location Data - Pathways and trails mapped within the scene\n- Environmental Data - Air quality\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-comments\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Discuss:** *Share an example of data that could be collected from one of the scenarios. Why might this data be useful?*\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-lightbulb-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Discussion Goal:** Students suggest ways that the data can be used. For example, in the rainy city scenario, they might suggest that the number of vehicles on the street might help city planners identify peak traffic times and design better traffic flow solutions. In the restaurant kitchen scenario, the movements of staff could help inform the kitchen layout to minimize traffic and improve workflow efficiency. In the nature scenario, the temperature or air quality could be tracked over time.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Introduce types of data that computer systems can collect.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Introduce the lesson objectives.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Introduce the Question of the Day."
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "c475ed09-bee8-44ce-9c44-df8b0b887410",
        "lesson_activity.key": "71dec560-ccd5-447c-baab-708cb9b4b2f6"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "746d2b43-c0d0-463c-931b-979c85709807",
      "position": 1,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:**  Place students into groups of three or four.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-file-text-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Distribute:** Give each group a copy of the Data in Computer Systems activity guide.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Students choose one of the stations. With their group, they read the station activity card. This card sets up unique challenges or problems faced by different careers. Students should complete the**Empathize with the User**section of their activity guide.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Students should complete the Define the Data and Ideate a Solution sections of the activity guide.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Repeat the activity, allowing students to select a new station. Encourage them to add different data ideas to the station's sticky notes.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-file-text-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Distribute:** Give each group a copy of the Data in Computer Systems activity guide.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Define *sensor*.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-desktop\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Transition:** Direct students to Lesson 7, Level 1. Students work on posing questions about data, sensors, and their role in a computer system. They should research sensors that came up as part of their solution to their scenarios that they explored in the station activity.\n",
        "progression_name": "Sensors and AI Chatbot"
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "746d2b43-c0d0-463c-931b-979c85709807",
        "lesson_activity.key": "7606a98c-2082-4165-adf8-202c66f1bf5a"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "3e7c4562-82a1-442b-9e0a-8e75cffcb6c1",
      "position": 2,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Students rotate around the room for 4 minutes, sharing information about one of the sensors that they encountered with a classmate, and getting information about a different sensor back in return. Note: students should not feel obligated to complete the entire chart. It should be used as a way to document their learning experience based on the sensors that were applicable to their station."
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "3e7c4562-82a1-442b-9e0a-8e75cffcb6c1",
        "lesson_activity.key": "7606a98c-2082-4165-adf8-202c66f1bf5a"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "d01f77c8-c7b2-4244-8ec8-a833709051eb",
      "position": 3,
      "properties": {
        "progression_name": "Student Survey"
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "d01f77c8-c7b2-4244-8ec8-a833709051eb",
        "lesson_activity.key": "7606a98c-2082-4165-adf8-202c66f1bf5a"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "14d52a76-aa9e-4ddb-b265-53b9fe003662",
      "position": 1,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Review the learning objectives.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Have students write one key insight or takeaway from today's lesson that relates to the Question of the Day. This can be completed in the Unit Guide, under the Question of the Day section. Have them share their takeaways with a partner or with the class."
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "14d52a76-aa9e-4ddb-b265-53b9fe003662",
        "lesson_activity.key": "a943e169-0eb2-4175-9d93-461e9d2f6da4"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "dce3a111-f39f-488d-9e12-33a13d090d26",
      "position": 1,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Put students into groups of four.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-file-text-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Distribute:** Give each group of students 20 to 25 UNO cards.",
        "tips": [
          {
            "type": "teachingTip",
            "markdown": "If you don't have UNO cards, there are digital card templates you can print and cut out for the activity. You can also use regular playing cards as an alternative. "
          }
        ]
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "dce3a111-f39f-488d-9e12-33a13d090d26",
        "lesson_activity.key": "5146c402-1782-4511-bec6-03a4170d45ce"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "a3b84abc-22e0-4dcd-8303-ab9d408c9985",
      "position": 2,
      "properties": {
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "a3b84abc-22e0-4dcd-8303-ab9d408c9985",
        "lesson_activity.key": "5146c402-1782-4511-bec6-03a4170d45ce"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "ddccd8bf-fd07-4f18-8df7-7cb7d025b010",
      "position": 3,
      "properties": {
        "description": "Your task is to sort the cards in ascending order by number. Take your time and focus on organizing your deck.",
        "remarks": true
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "ddccd8bf-fd07-4f18-8df7-7cb7d025b010",
        "lesson_activity.key": "5146c402-1782-4511-bec6-03a4170d45ce"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "b1126a33-99e0-4a32-b333-125c7f5f84d1",
      "position": 4,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This**: Play the music clip (blue volume icon) during this round as students work.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This**: Students sort their cards by number in ascending order.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-comments\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Discuss**: *What patterns or insights did you notice after sorting?*\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-lightbulb-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Discussion Goal**: Listen for responses like, \"The cards were easier to analyze,\" or \"It helped us quickly identify the highest and lowest values.\""
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "b1126a33-99e0-4a32-b333-125c7f5f84d1",
        "lesson_activity.key": "5146c402-1782-4511-bec6-03a4170d45ce"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "1744f32f-5c65-4296-9ced-65d6db711624",
      "position": 5,
      "properties": {
        "description": "Now, choose one color and filter your deck to include only the cards of that color. Set aside any cards that don't match.",
        "remarks": true
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "1744f32f-5c65-4296-9ced-65d6db711624",
        "lesson_activity.key": "5146c402-1782-4511-bec6-03a4170d45ce"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "5ec8cc93-958e-44ae-870b-d273a1f11cad",
      "position": 6,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This**: Play the music clip (blue volume icon) during this round as students work.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This**: Students will choose one color and filter their deck to include only the cards of that color, setting aside the others.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-comments\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Discuss**: *What patterns or insights did you notice after filtering?*\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-lightbulb-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Discussion Goal:** Listen for responses like, \"We could focus on a specific group of cards,\" or \"It showed which colors had more or fewer cards.\""
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "5ec8cc93-958e-44ae-870b-d273a1f11cad",
        "lesson_activity.key": "5146c402-1782-4511-bec6-03a4170d45ce"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "2014c132-4fb1-43ca-bd60-826e8abdbf4b",
      "position": 7,
      "properties": {
        "description": "Now, count how many cards you have for each color. Record the totals for red, blue, yellow, and green.",
        "remarks": true
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "2014c132-4fb1-43ca-bd60-826e8abdbf4b",
        "lesson_activity.key": "5146c402-1782-4511-bec6-03a4170d45ce"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "26ec52f7-d560-4df7-a46a-78c7f728c52a",
      "position": 8,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This**: Play the music clip (blue volume icon) during this round as students work.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Students will count how many cards they have for each color and record the totals for red, blue, yellow, and green.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-comments\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Discuss**: *What patterns or insights did you notice after counting?*\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-lightbulb-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Discussion Goal**: Listen for insights like, \"Red and blue cards made up most of the deck,\" or \"It helped us see which colors were more common.\"\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This**: Introduce the learning objectives.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This**: Introduce the Question of the Day."
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "26ec52f7-d560-4df7-a46a-78c7f728c52a",
        "lesson_activity.key": "5146c402-1782-4511-bec6-03a4170d45ce"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "827d90c2-4f15-4c8a-a8fc-09673b321e77",
      "position": 1,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Place students in pairs.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-file-text-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Distribute:** Give each student a Processing Library Data activity guide.",
        "duration": "20",
        "name": "Processing Library Data"
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "827d90c2-4f15-4c8a-a8fc-09673b321e77",
        "lesson_activity.key": "3d1f84be-d0ec-4e72-b558-d2291e9b509f"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "e7c66749-7e19-4375-b56b-9e95a0759775",
      "position": 2,
      "properties": {
        "description": "Imagine you’re a librarian who needs to make decisions quickly, like recommending books to visitors or identifying which books are rarely checked out. You can’t rely on manual sorting all the time, especially when dealing with thousands of records. That’s where computer systems and computational tasks come in. Today, we’ll work with a dataset about a library’s book collection and use computational processes to uncover patterns and make data-driven decisions, just like a computer system would. In this activity, you’ll analyze a dataset step by step, just like a computer system processes data. We’ll use a flowchart to break the problem into clear steps. Let’s walk through an example together to get started.",
        "remarks": true
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "e7c66749-7e19-4375-b56b-9e95a0759775",
        "lesson_activity.key": "3d1f84be-d0ec-4e72-b558-d2291e9b509f"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "7b8aebd9-fb2d-48f4-9711-c024549572f7",
      "position": 3,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-desktop\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Transition**: Direct students to open Lesson 8, Level 1. Walk students through solving the first choice level using the following steps:\n- **Define the goal:** A new visitor wants to know the hottest books to start reading.\n- **Identify the relevant data:** Popularity Score column.\n- **Choose the action (verb):** Sort.\n- **Apply the action:** Use the spreadsheet to **sort** by descending order of Popularity Score.\n- **Describe the output:** Sort by descending order of Popularity Score.\n- **Describe the output:** The books are now listed from most popular to least popular.\n- **Reflect on insights**: This helps the library highlight the most popular books to new visitors.",
        "progression_name": "Processing Library Data"
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "7b8aebd9-fb2d-48f4-9711-c024549572f7",
        "lesson_activity.key": "3d1f84be-d0ec-4e72-b558-d2291e9b509f"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "3b4049a3-d5a3-4269-bed9-6a273d12a29a",
      "position": 4,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This**: Model filling out the Madlib template on chart paper or the board for the first scenario: “The system needs to [show the hottest books to visitors]. To do this, it will [Sort] the [Popularity Score column] by [descending order]. The system will then produce [a list of books ranked by popularity] so that [visitors know the best books to start with].”"
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "3b4049a3-d5a3-4269-bed9-6a273d12a29a",
        "lesson_activity.key": "3d1f84be-d0ec-4e72-b558-d2291e9b509f"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "7b689fb1-03ec-4f6d-9f28-97ffdfa24323",
      "position": 5,
      "properties": {
        "description": "Now it’s your turn! Work with your partner to complete three library data choice levels. For each scenario, follow the steps we just practiced: define the goal, choose the action, identify the relevant data, apply the action, describe the output, and reflect on the insights. Don’t forget to complete the flowchart and Madlib template for each level!",
        "remarks": true
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "7b689fb1-03ec-4f6d-9f28-97ffdfa24323",
        "lesson_activity.key": "3d1f84be-d0ec-4e72-b558-d2291e9b509f"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "85c6a492-adaa-4716-b5aa-6051f45af4d6",
      "position": 6,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This**: Students complete the remaining library data choice levels in Lesson 8, Level 1. They use their activity guide to write down the steps for three of the choice levels, and fill out the Madlib template to summarize their process and results for three of the choice levels level."
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "85c6a492-adaa-4716-b5aa-6051f45af4d6",
        "lesson_activity.key": "3d1f84be-d0ec-4e72-b558-d2291e9b509f"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "142ba136-fea3-45cd-883a-c7221cbc9b1f",
      "position": 7,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-refresh\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Circulate**:\n- Observe students as they work through the scenarios.\n- Check that students are filling out their flowchart worksheets and Madlib templates correctly.\n- Provide guidance or clarification if students are stuck on any step.",
        "tips": [
          {
            "type": "teachingTip",
            "markdown": "Encourage students to think back to the UNO card activity. Remind them how sorting, filtering, and aggregating helped them see patterns and make decisions with their cards. They can apply the same strategies to the library dataset."
          }
        ]
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "142ba136-fea3-45cd-883a-c7221cbc9b1f",
        "lesson_activity.key": "3d1f84be-d0ec-4e72-b558-d2291e9b509f"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "5885dd2b-5a72-4974-b20b-7791b68de3ba",
      "position": 8,
      "properties": {
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "5885dd2b-5a72-4974-b20b-7791b68de3ba",
        "lesson_activity.key": "3d1f84be-d0ec-4e72-b558-d2291e9b509f"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "aa2b8f8d-29cd-4531-a92f-038bd25e4777",
      "position": 9,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This**: Once students have completed their scenarios, lead a review as a class. Ask student pairs to share their answers, focusing on the flowchart steps and the Madlib templates. Highlight and clarify any differences or commonalities in their findings."
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "aa2b8f8d-29cd-4531-a92f-038bd25e4777",
        "lesson_activity.key": "3d1f84be-d0ec-4e72-b558-d2291e9b509f"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "e92dd3e9-b34e-40b5-96b0-74cace151b2b",
      "position": 10,
      "properties": {
        "description": "Let’s take some time to reflect on what you’ve learned. You’ll answer three free-response questions to compare the benefits and limitations of manual and computational data processing. Think about how the tools and methods we used today improve efficiency, accuracy, and help us handle larger datasets.",
        "duration": "10",
        "name": "Reflection",
        "remarks": true
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "e92dd3e9-b34e-40b5-96b0-74cace151b2b",
        "lesson_activity.key": "3d1f84be-d0ec-4e72-b558-d2291e9b509f"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "c2399cd5-702e-4830-a8db-75e3993b0f8d",
      "position": 11,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-desktop\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Transition:** Direct students to Lesson 8, Level 2 to respond to the reflection questions on Levels 2, 3, and 4.",
        "progression_name": "Reflection"
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "c2399cd5-702e-4830-a8db-75e3993b0f8d",
        "lesson_activity.key": "3d1f84be-d0ec-4e72-b558-d2291e9b509f"
      }
    },
