    {
      "key": "e701d697-900c-4b4d-b862-635b827ba641",
      "position": 1,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This**: Review the learning objectives.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This**: Review the Question of the Day.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-file-text-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Distribute:** Give each student an index card or small piece of paper."
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "e701d697-900c-4b4d-b862-635b827ba641",
        "lesson_activity.key": "f88e8ef0-4c64-4d5e-8c36-f88de62fe03c"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "75ba5d08-8e9f-430b-acde-d7f014bb66c6",
      "position": 2,
      "properties": {
        "description": "We’re going to watch a short video that connects what we’ve learned today to a real-world example. While you watch, think about the questions on the screen and take notes. You’ll answer all three questions as your exit ticket.",
        "remarks": true
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "75ba5d08-8e9f-430b-acde-d7f014bb66c6",
        "lesson_activity.key": "f88e8ef0-4c64-4d5e-8c36-f88de62fe03c"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "470388e3-eab1-4609-ad18-8016c91c6a12",
      "position": 3,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-video-camera\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Video**: Show the video \"This AI coach can show tennis players how to up their game\".\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Students watch the video carefully and answer the questions on their index card."
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "470388e3-eab1-4609-ad18-8016c91c6a12",
        "lesson_activity.key": "f88e8ef0-4c64-4d5e-8c36-f88de62fe03c"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "361b67fa-2333-48aa-8248-004b6f2b3f17",
      "position": 1,
      "properties": {
        "description": "AI helps us process large amounts of data to make predictions, from recommending what to watch on Netflix to forecasting the weather. Today, we’re going to explore how AI processes data and how the hardware behind AI impacts its performance.",
        "remarks": true
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "361b67fa-2333-48aa-8248-004b6f2b3f17",
        "lesson_activity.key": "75005b55-6ad4-4824-87fb-7f8952eebea7"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "24b7e3fa-0718-4f03-8306-b0a637356343",
      "position": 2,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-video-camera\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Video:** Show the video \"Can AI help us predict extreme weather\" from 0:00 to 1:39.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-comments\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Discuss:** *What types of atmospheric data gets collected by satellites, weather stations, and buoys?*\n- Round Robin Sharing: Invite students to share one data type. If time allows, go around the room or ask for volunteers.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-lightbulb-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Discussion Goal:** Students should mention temperature, wind speed, humidity, air pressure, and cloud images as key data inputs.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-video-camera\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Video:** Show the video \"Can AI help us predict extreme weather\" from 3:54 to 5:30.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-comments\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Discuss:** Click through the animated slide to display the prompts.\n- *What benefits are there to using AI to make weather forecasts?*\n- *Do you think AI forecasts always get it right?*\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-lightbulb-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Discussion Goal:** AI speeds up analysis, making predictions in seconds instead of weeks. AI models prioritize accuracy and learn from penalties for incorrect predictions. Ultimately, whether it’s done by a human or by AI it’s still a prediction or educated guess about what will happen. This particular forecasting AI prioritizes safer, more likely outcomes and can miss catastrophic weather events. This is especially true because these AI models are trained on the past 40 years of weather data and we currently have (and will continue to have) more unpredictable, extreme weather events due to climate change.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This**: Introduce the lesson objectives.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This**: Introduce the Question of the Day."
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "24b7e3fa-0718-4f03-8306-b0a637356343",
        "lesson_activity.key": "75005b55-6ad4-4824-87fb-7f8952eebea7"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "bc65bb5c-c5a9-4d59-b4c0-c58ec8404b02",
      "position": 1,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-file-text-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Distribute:** Give each student a How AI Uses Data activity guide.",
        "duration": "10",
        "name": "AI in the Real World"
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "bc65bb5c-c5a9-4d59-b4c0-c58ec8404b02",
        "lesson_activity.key": "0051b775-a409-423c-88a9-a970c41786e7"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "de316807-ae8c-4de6-bab9-95d6a86a595b",
      "position": 2,
      "properties": {
        "description": "AI systems use data to make decisions in real-world applications. Let’s explore how different AI models function and what data they rely on.",
        "remarks": true
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "de316807-ae8c-4de6-bab9-95d6a86a595b",
        "lesson_activity.key": "0051b775-a409-423c-88a9-a970c41786e7"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "8c3b895e-ce0e-40eb-9cd7-5cf92372e629",
      "position": 3,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Put students into groups of 3-4. Assign each group an AI use case:\n- Voice Assistants (Alexa/Siri): AI processes voice input and generates responses.\n- Self-Driving Cars: AI uses sensor data to navigate roads.\n- Medical Imaging AI: AI scans medical images for disease detection.\n- AI Translation Tools: AI converts text/audio between languages.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-desktop\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Transition:**  Direct students to open Lesson 9, Level 1. In their groups, students will watch a video about the assigned technology and answer the following questions in their activity guide:\n- What is the AI model doing in this scenario?\n- What type of data is being input?\n- What is the decision being made? In other words, what does this AI system do with the data?\n- Why does this task require speed and scale?",
        "progression_name": "Explore an AI Model"
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "8c3b895e-ce0e-40eb-9cd7-5cf92372e629",
        "lesson_activity.key": "0051b775-a409-423c-88a9-a970c41786e7"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "9cfd3c25-e816-4ae0-8683-869518d09dd3",
      "position": 4,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-refresh\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Circulate:** Make sure that all students are able to answer all questions. At the end of the lesson, students will do a jigsaw activity to share out their answers."
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "9cfd3c25-e816-4ae0-8683-869518d09dd3",
        "lesson_activity.key": "0051b775-a409-423c-88a9-a970c41786e7"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "61022b18-bd6f-4f34-866a-dfee56bcad5e",
      "position": 5,
      "properties": {
        "description": " <i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:**  Define*processing unit*.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This**: Explain that just like different tools are suited for different jobs, AI models need the right kind of hardware to function efficiently. Computers use different types of processing units depending on the task. Some are more flexible, meaning they can handle a variety of tasks, while others are built for efficiency, meaning they are designed for a specific purpose and run faster with less energy. Let’s explore how these four processing units work.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This**: Click through the animated slide to introduce CPUs.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This**: Click through the animated slide to introduce GPUs.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This**: Click through the animated slide to introduce FPGA.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This**: Click through the animated slide to introduce ASICs.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-desktop\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Transition:** Direct students to open Lesson 9, Level 2. Students will select a computing task from a list of options and choose a processing unit (CPU, GPU, FPGA, or ASIC) to complete the task. They will observe the benchmarking results and receive a performance score based on their selection. Students should record their observations in their activity guide, analyzing which processor performed best for each task and why.",
        "duration": "15",
        "name": "AI Hardware",
        "progression_name": "Processing Unit Battle"
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "61022b18-bd6f-4f34-866a-dfee56bcad5e",
        "lesson_activity.key": "0051b775-a409-423c-88a9-a970c41786e7"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "d849d6a4-6142-4978-a4f0-26cfcd68f899",
      "position": 6,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This**: Direct students to Lesson 9, Level 3. Students use AI Chat to research and choose the best AI hardware for their AI model. They record their findings and respond to guided questions in the Determine AI Hardware section of their activity guide.",
        "progression_name": "Determine AI Hardware"
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "d849d6a4-6142-4978-a4f0-26cfcd68f899",
        "lesson_activity.key": "0051b775-a409-423c-88a9-a970c41786e7"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "8424dc72-16d9-41d3-8570-e0a458e3fb15",
      "position": 7,
      "properties": {
        "progression_name": "Student Survey"
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "8424dc72-16d9-41d3-8570-e0a458e3fb15",
        "lesson_activity.key": "0051b775-a409-423c-88a9-a970c41786e7"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "f81c8a2a-5e24-45c8-a8da-764c7d999d8a",
      "position": 1,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This**: Review the lesson objectives.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This**: Review the Question of the Day.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:**  Form new groups (1 student from each AI case study per group). Each student presents their AI system, explaining what the AI model does, what kind of data it processes, and what hardware best supports it and why.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-refresh\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Circulate**: Ensure students explain why specific hardware is best suited for their AI model.",
        "tips": [
          {
            "type": "teachingTip",
            "markdown": "Encourage students to compare AI hardware choices in terms of speed, power consumption, and cost. Real-world constraints, such as affordability and energy efficiency, often determine the best hardware for an AI task."
          }
        ]
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "f81c8a2a-5e24-45c8-a8da-764c7d999d8a",
        "lesson_activity.key": "f5769da0-8f98-4648-a852-fc3ab6dab48c"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "06c5cee0-8e89-4d32-918c-75404d886439",
      "position": 1,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:**  Play the video (0:00 - 1:48).\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-comments\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Discuss:** *What are some other examples of IoT devices you've heard about or used?*\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-lightbulb-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Discussion Goal:** Get students to realize they interact with IoT devices and systems in different parts of their lives. For example, a smartwatch tracks your steps and sends the information to an app on your phone, or a smart thermostat adjusts the temperature in your home based on the weather outside.",
        "tips": [
          {
            "type": "teachingTip",
            "markdown": "Videos are used throughout the curriculum to spark discussions, supplement key concepts with additional explanations and examples, and expose students to the various roles and backgrounds of individuals in computer science.\n\nWhile interacting with the video, turn on closed captioning so students can also read along as they watch.\n\nTo encourage active engagement and reflection, use one or more of the strategies discussed in the [**Guide to Curriculum Videos**](https://docs.google.com/document/d/1Y-kGl_pc2afuSBKhKkdulu53X50mc7T-RQZA4vGLpY4/edit?usp=sharing)."
          }
        ]
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "06c5cee0-8e89-4d32-918c-75404d886439",
        "lesson_activity.key": "d96e72c1-d0a6-4e1e-af71-61d94a1243f5"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "7c2cd77d-35bf-4897-8f9e-e0fcad3fa0cd",
      "position": 2,
      "properties": {
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "7c2cd77d-35bf-4897-8f9e-e0fcad3fa0cd",
        "lesson_activity.key": "d96e72c1-d0a6-4e1e-af71-61d94a1243f5"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "7054b8c4-2a72-42b1-911c-e45e1aa79b9e",
      "position": 3,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Define *Internet of Things (IoT)*.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Introduce the learning objectives.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Introduce the Question of the Day."
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "7054b8c4-2a72-42b1-911c-e45e1aa79b9e",
        "lesson_activity.key": "d96e72c1-d0a6-4e1e-af71-61d94a1243f5"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "183a172d-6ef3-455e-86bb-fe299a9fb53c",
      "position": 1,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:**  Place students in pairs.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-file-text-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Distribute:** Give each student a copy of The Internet of Things activity guide.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Introduce examples of standalone devices, such as pedometers or digital thermometers. Then give students examples of IoT devices, such as an Alexa speaker or a Ring camera.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Instruct students to choose one pair of devices and respond to the first question on the activity guide.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-comments\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Discuss:** *What are different ways that you might connect a device in order to communicate data?*\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-lightbulb-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Discussion Goal:** This should be a quick whole-class discussion to activate prior knowledge before reviewing some of the different methods that IoT devices communicate to the internet.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-file-text-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Distribute:** Give each student a copy of The Transmission of Data Unit Guide.",
        "duration": "15",
        "name": "Exploring IoT Systems, Hardware, and Privacy Concerns"
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "183a172d-6ef3-455e-86bb-fe299a9fb53c",
        "lesson_activity.key": "9d500142-e1d5-4266-a833-f59d74dfa14e"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "1b19233a-b977-422b-85ba-f7e378a813d7",
      "position": 2,
      "properties": {
        "description": "Once a device has data, it must be transmitted in some fashion to be processed. One way to determine what transmission system is best for a given IoT device is to gauge the range that the data needs to travel.",
        "remarks": true
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "1b19233a-b977-422b-85ba-f7e378a813d7",
        "lesson_activity.key": "9d500142-e1d5-4266-a833-f59d74dfa14e"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "734542dd-8db2-4fa7-99f1-d9497bd67f37",
      "position": 3,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:**  Introduce the examples for short-range communications.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Have students complete the corresponding section of their unit guide. For each of the examples presented, have students brainstorm a device or two that uses that communication protocol.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Read the examples for short-range communications. Have students complete the corresponding section of their unit guide.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Read the examples for medium-range communications. Have students complete the corresponding section of their unit guide.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Read the examples for long-range communications. Have students complete the corresponding section of their unit guide.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Read the examples for long-range communications. Have students complete the corresponding section of their unit guide.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Instruct students to finish the remaining two questions on their activity guide:\n- How might the device transmit data, if at all?\n- What privacy risks might this device introduce?\n- With internet connectivity, how might a device’s functionality change?\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-desktop\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Transition:** Direct students to Lesson 10, Level 1 to respond to the question.",
        "progression_name": "Security, Privacy, and Data Ownership",
        "tips": [
          {
            "type": "assessmentOpportunity",
            "markdown": "This level can be used to assess students' ability to analyze the privacy and ethical implications of IoT systems."
          }
        ]
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "734542dd-8db2-4fa7-99f1-d9497bd67f37",
        "lesson_activity.key": "9d500142-e1d5-4266-a833-f59d74dfa14e"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "f2357d1a-db80-4045-9ac6-4e599a91de45",
      "position": 4,
      "properties": {
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "f2357d1a-db80-4045-9ac6-4e599a91de45",
        "lesson_activity.key": "9d500142-e1d5-4266-a833-f59d74dfa14e"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "c889648d-af1a-4c40-a7d1-4acb9e765a16",
      "position": 5,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-file-text-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Distribute:** Have each student make a copy of the Smart Classroom Template.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Introduce the Design a Smart Classroom activity.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Explain the steps students need to take to complete the activity. Refer to the example that is in the template.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Have students participate in a Give One, Get One to share the innovation they developed. Students should share the innovation as well as the data it collects, how it transmits that information, and any privacy or security concerns that might exist.",
        "duration": "20",
        "name": "Design a Smart Classroom",
        "tips": [
          {
            "type": "teachingTip",
            "markdown": "During a Give One, Get One activity, students should wander the classroom while the music is playing, find a partner, share their smart classroom innovation, and listen to the innovation proposed by their partner. While the music is still playing, students should repeat the exercise with a new partner. If there is extra time, possible differentiations for this activity include giving one piece of feedback to their partner, and leading the activity into a class discussion where some students share a refined version of their idea with the class based on partner discussion and feedback."
          },
          {
            "type": "assessmentOpportunity",
            "markdown": "The Smart Classroom activity can be used to assess students' understanding of various types of IoT systems, the hardware needed for these systems, and their applications in real-world contexts."
          }
        ]
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "c889648d-af1a-4c40-a7d1-4acb9e765a16",
        "lesson_activity.key": "9d500142-e1d5-4266-a833-f59d74dfa14e"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "66e42a1b-5196-466a-8a9a-dc12b862008f",
      "position": 1,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Review the learning objectives.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Review the Question of the Day.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-comments\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Discuss:** Click through the animated slide to display the prompts.\n- *Give a recommendation to someone thinking about designing their home using smart devices. What are some things they should consider?*\n- *What will be easier or safer?*\n- *What will be more challenging or dangerous?*\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-lightbulb-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Discussion Goal:** The goal of this discussion is to help students think critically about the benefits and challenges of designing a smart home. Encourage them to balance convenience and security in their recommendations by considering factors such as privacy risks, data security, and device compatibility. Guide students to explore how smart devices can enhance safety, such as through security cameras and alarms, while also introducing potential risks like hacking and data breaches. Additionally, prompt them to think about long-term costs, reliability, and ethical implications, helping them develop well-rounded recommendations for someone considering a smart home."
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "66e42a1b-5196-466a-8a9a-dc12b862008f",
        "lesson_activity.key": "8e72682c-7167-41c5-9de7-8a8e24051421"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "b3aa6e01-5d49-45ab-a0b6-648896e2033c",
      "position": 2,
      "properties": {
        "progression_name": "Survey"
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "b3aa6e01-5d49-45ab-a0b6-648896e2033c",
        "lesson_activity.key": "8e72682c-7167-41c5-9de7-8a8e24051421"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "4f2b290c-8674-4dbe-be8a-e02b97496208",
      "position": 1,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-video-camera\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Video:**  Show the video \"Guerilla Testing with Usability Cafe\"\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-comments\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> Questions to Consider with the **Video:** *How might usability testing look different when testing a physical device or system that is not run solely on a computer, tablet, or phone?*\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-lightbulb-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Discussion Goal:** Listen for students to bring up challenges when testing something that has many parts and might need to be done in specific environments and/or under specific circumstances.",
        "tips": [
          {
            "type": "teachingTip",
            "markdown": "To encourage active engagement and reflection, use one or more of the strategies discussed in the [**Guide to Curriculum Videos**](https://docs.google.com/document/d/1Y-kGl_pc2afuSBKhKkdulu53X50mc7T-RQZA4vGLpY4/edit?usp=sharing)."
          }
        ]
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "4f2b290c-8674-4dbe-be8a-e02b97496208",
        "lesson_activity.key": "7f17e81c-5804-4920-bdc7-10154afbe23a"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "04ef818d-9c5d-49ac-89d3-c6ea333dde7c",
      "position": 2,
      "properties": {
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "04ef818d-9c5d-49ac-89d3-c6ea333dde7c",
        "lesson_activity.key": "7f17e81c-5804-4920-bdc7-10154afbe23a"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "bc16583d-6e13-4d46-b8ec-2eed60929e41",
      "position": 3,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Define *user testing*.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Introduce the lesson objectives.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Introduce the Question of the Day."
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "bc16583d-6e13-4d46-b8ec-2eed60929e41",
        "lesson_activity.key": "7f17e81c-5804-4920-bdc7-10154afbe23a"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "2b473c88-3f70-4cde-bcbb-1f24e5b9fd79",
      "position": 1,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-desktop\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Transition:**  Direct students to Lesson 11, Level 1. Students look at user testing results for a product and pull out the main themes.",
        "duration": "15",
        "name": "User Testing Data",
        "progression_name": "User Testing Results"
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "2b473c88-3f70-4cde-bcbb-1f24e5b9fd79",
        "lesson_activity.key": "894571e9-beab-4d44-8397-488fdddf2150"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "95860288-3cd0-49cf-b170-255b215f30e2",
      "position": 2,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-refresh\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Circulate:** Walk around to ensure students are looking at all the types of data (observations, user survey response tables, and feedback) when doing their analysis."
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "95860288-3cd0-49cf-b170-255b215f30e2",
        "lesson_activity.key": "894571e9-beab-4d44-8397-488fdddf2150"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "d048f952-ca51-46c5-9c7c-b1e85b53070c",
      "position": 3,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Direct students to Lesson 11, Level 2 to work with the chatbot to help summarize the same data they just looked at.",
        "progression_name": "Using AI to Analyze Data"
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "d048f952-ca51-46c5-9c7c-b1e85b53070c",
        "lesson_activity.key": "894571e9-beab-4d44-8397-488fdddf2150"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "2a559e6c-872b-4077-8700-703cdcd9ad68",
      "position": 4,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-comments\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Discuss:** *How is AI helpful when processing user testing data? What would have been difficult to do without it?*\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-lightbulb-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Discussion Goal:** Listen for students to point out for when the chatbot noticed something that they did not or for times when AI summarized the results more clearly. Also make sure to make space in the conversation for evaluating the AI responses and having students share the tips they used to help the AI work better at generating insights from the data or when the AI made incorrect statements from the data.\n\nDepending on where the discussion goes, here are some potential follow-up questions to engage the class with:\n- Which summary do you think you would include a report to the team working on this product, yours or the chatbots? Why?\n- How do you think your summary would have been different if you’d used AI to summarize the data first before doing your own analysis?"
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "2a559e6c-872b-4077-8700-703cdcd9ad68",
        "lesson_activity.key": "894571e9-beab-4d44-8397-488fdddf2150"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "4ec93f90-067e-4258-9795-c2c05c338cbd",
      "position": 5,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Have a student read the scenario out loud.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-desktop\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Transition:**  Direct students to Lesson 11, Level 3. Students will see the same scenario, along with four choices for how Alice should respond to this situation.",
        "duration": "20",
        "name": "What's Next",
        "progression_name": "Alice's Scenario"
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "4ec93f90-067e-4258-9795-c2c05c338cbd",
        "lesson_activity.key": "894571e9-beab-4d44-8397-488fdddf2150"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "455bc5da-aeaa-4eeb-9eaa-56e167b74ea5",
      "position": 6,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-refresh\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Circulate:** Monitor students as they decide which option they think Alice should pick. When students have made a decision, the background of the app will turn green. When most students have green screens, return to the front of the room and use the “View Student Responses” button to project the class responses to the room. This graph can be used for the discussion on the next slide.",
        "tips": [
          {
            "type": "teachingTip",
            "markdown": "This level is designed to use the Student Summaries feature, which lets you view and display the responses from the class. This requires having this level opened on your computer and, in the teacher panel, selecting the current section of your classes. [**Click here to learn more about viewing student responses**](https://support.code.org/hc/en-us/articles/14544890300301-Can-I-see-a-summary-of-all-my-students-responses-for-question-based-levels). If you are unable to use the student summaries, you can also run this as an unplugged discussion where students vote in their seats or move to different corners of the room depending on their responses. Ultimately, students need a way to take a stand and be ready to discuss their opinions in the next slide."
          }
        ]
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "455bc5da-aeaa-4eeb-9eaa-56e167b74ea5",
        "lesson_activity.key": "894571e9-beab-4d44-8397-488fdddf2150"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "b002e689-1c41-4c5b-8731-75e6cf24f979",
      "position": 7,
      "properties": {
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "b002e689-1c41-4c5b-8731-75e6cf24f979",
        "lesson_activity.key": "894571e9-beab-4d44-8397-488fdddf2150"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "dba7a9a1-107c-4db2-8487-80c52b7e3efa",
      "position": 8,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-comments\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Discuss:**  What should the next steps be for Alice?\n- Use the information from the student summary screen (or other class voting method) to guide the conversation. Invite a student from each area to share their rationale.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-lightbulb-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Discussion Goal:** There is no definitive right answer here, as long as students can explain and justify their thoughts. Some students may choose option A, given that the device works as intended for the specific target user – gamers with mobility issues. Other students may gravitate towards options B or C - either fixing it after launch, or delaying in order to fix - because it doesn’t work as well as it should for all users and it should be made more equitable before launching.",
        "tips": [
          {
            "type": "teachingTip",
            "markdown": "Regardless of what answer students pick, the more important goal is for students to recognize that there are still important decisions - made by humans - before their technology should be released to the public, and this exercise introduces students to some of the choices they could make. Additionally, students should discuss who to prioritize when making updates. In this case, should they prioritize the positive feedback they received from mobility challenged gamers (primary user) or from other gamers (secondary users)?"
          }
        ]
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "dba7a9a1-107c-4db2-8487-80c52b7e3efa",
        "lesson_activity.key": "894571e9-beab-4d44-8397-488fdddf2150"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "d7f05a1f-05b5-48b2-854d-d76bd6f89599",
      "position": 9,
      "properties": {
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "d7f05a1f-05b5-48b2-854d-d76bd6f89599",
        "lesson_activity.key": "894571e9-beab-4d44-8397-488fdddf2150"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "87b77df0-73d4-47df-b724-3805a7a32802",
      "position": 10,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Have a student read the scenario out loud.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-desktop\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Transition:** Direct students to Lesson 11, Level 4. Students will see the same scenario, along with four choices for how Josh should respond to this situation.",
        "progression_name": "Josh's Scenario"
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "87b77df0-73d4-47df-b724-3805a7a32802",
        "lesson_activity.key": "894571e9-beab-4d44-8397-488fdddf2150"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "5d7e8fc2-4653-4d62-bfe7-e278ed5c3269",
      "position": 11,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-refresh\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Circulate:** Monitor students as they decide which option they think Josh should pick. When students have made a decision, the background of the app will turn green. When most students have green screens, return to the front of the room and use the “View Student Responses” button to project the class responses to the room. This graph can be used for the discussion on the next slide."
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "5d7e8fc2-4653-4d62-bfe7-e278ed5c3269",
        "lesson_activity.key": "894571e9-beab-4d44-8397-488fdddf2150"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "3b7364da-9b8e-4235-9aaf-94791dad199c",
      "position": 12,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-comments\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Discuss:** *What should Josh do about his device?*\n- Use the information from the student summary screen (or other class voting method) to guide the conversation. Invite a student from each area to share their rationale.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-lightbulb-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Discussion Goal:** This answer tends to have a more moral or ethical component, since the technology shows a clear gender bias against women, who are more likely to have higher pitched voices and therefore not be able to use the technology. Students will likely gravitate towards options C or D, opting to cancel or pause implementation so more testing can be conducted and the harm can be addressed before it is released.",
        "tips": [
          {
            "type": "teachingTip",
            "markdown": "This scenario is based on real-world events where this exact situation unfolded - multiple car companies released voice activated phone systems knowing that they were unlikely to work for women -you can read more about that here. The real-life version of this may be surprising to students - the companies initially ignored the user testing feedback and went with option (B), releasing the voice-recognition system to the public first before making changes. It was only after several years that these harmful effects were addressed. You can decide if you want to highlight this scenario with students and discuss the approach to user testing: “Improvements were made first for males, then females, then Midwestern speakers. Finally it was adjusted for Southern speakers and people from New England.”"
          }
        ]
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "3b7364da-9b8e-4235-9aaf-94791dad199c",
        "lesson_activity.key": "894571e9-beab-4d44-8397-488fdddf2150"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "22da2228-e653-41f5-bf9a-011d7c581667",
      "position": 13,
      "properties": {
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "22da2228-e653-41f5-bf9a-011d7c581667",
        "lesson_activity.key": "894571e9-beab-4d44-8397-488fdddf2150"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "758566a5-373a-41f6-a150-86c169c656ea",
      "position": 14,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Have a student read the scenario out loud.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-desktop\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Transition:**  Direct students to Lesson 11, Level 5. Here is another scenario where students can explore and discuss how to respond. The scenario is also provided on the next slide.",
        "progression_name": "Lydia's Scenario"
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "758566a5-373a-41f6-a150-86c169c656ea",
        "lesson_activity.key": "894571e9-beab-4d44-8397-488fdddf2150"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "b134969c-d4dd-4300-b2f3-143a51d59dfc",
      "position": 15,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-refresh\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Circulate:** Monitor students as they decide which option to pick. When students have made a decision, the background of the app will turn green. When most students have green screens, return to the front of the room and use the “View Student Responses” button to project the class responses to the room. This graph can be used for the discussion on the next slide."
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "b134969c-d4dd-4300-b2f3-143a51d59dfc",
        "lesson_activity.key": "894571e9-beab-4d44-8397-488fdddf2150"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "4731eef4-e8dd-4287-bd64-9d5df861cb9a",
      "position": 16,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-comments\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Discuss:** *What should the next steps be for Lydia?*\n- Use the information from the student summary screen (or other class voting method) to guide the conversation. Invite a student from each area to share their rationale.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-lightbulb-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Discussion Goal:** Similar to the previous scenario, students will likely gravitate towards options C or D, opting to cancel or pause implementation so more testing can be conducted and the harm can be addressed before it is released. Because this device excludes a group of users who are color blind, launching it as is means that the device is inequitable and not accessible for all users. Students should consider how Lydia can improve her design by considering all intended users.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-comments\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Discuss:** *Give one example of something you heard a classmate share that made you think about one of the scenarios differently.*\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-lightbulb-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Discussion Goal:** Listen for students noting when someone shared something from a different perspective. You may need to push students to explore this part a bit more, but the goal here is for them to understand the collaborative decision making with a group of people who bring different perspectives leads to better outcomes."
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "4731eef4-e8dd-4287-bd64-9d5df861cb9a",
        "lesson_activity.key": "894571e9-beab-4d44-8397-488fdddf2150"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "da833670-fd36-48c8-9032-a7e7e480b255",
      "position": 17,
      "properties": {
        "progression_name": "Student Survey"
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "da833670-fd36-48c8-9032-a7e7e480b255",
        "lesson_activity.key": "894571e9-beab-4d44-8397-488fdddf2150"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "c7e7842b-cfbf-42c8-a07a-274397463e20",
      "position": 1,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Have students write down their top two reasons why user testing can improve a product in their unit guides.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Have students write down their top two answers for what happens when user testing is skipped in their unit guides.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-comments\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Discuss:** *What did you choose, and why?*\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-lightbulb-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Discussion Goal:** Listen for students to cite examples shared during the class period and/or personal experiences the students have had themselves as justifications for their answers.\n"
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "c7e7842b-cfbf-42c8-a07a-274397463e20",
        "lesson_activity.key": "20a385a9-da3a-45bd-bdfb-939895d48480"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "74f6c2f8-d421-4ada-ae63-8eeffcc5c406",
      "position": 1,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-video-camera\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Video:**  Show the video \"Ethics and AI: Privacy and the Future of Work\"\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Prompt students to consider the questions posed here as they watch the video.",
        "tips": [
          {
            "type": "teachingTip",
            "markdown": "To encourage active engagement and reflection, use one or more of the strategies discussed in the [**Guide to Curriculum Videos**](https://docs.google.com/document/d/1Y-kGl_pc2afuSBKhKkdulu53X50mc7T-RQZA4vGLpY4/edit?usp=sharing)."
          }
        ]
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "74f6c2f8-d421-4ada-ae63-8eeffcc5c406",
        "lesson_activity.key": "fa8bfc3c-5061-469b-b5c7-2bd34e394fba"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "b4a63911-2967-408b-b43b-74bd2d591e6c",
      "position": 2,
      "properties": {
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "b4a63911-2967-408b-b43b-74bd2d591e6c",
        "lesson_activity.key": "fa8bfc3c-5061-469b-b5c7-2bd34e394fba"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "6c84e17c-98ec-426c-bc2a-f9278891afe0",
      "position": 3,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-comments\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Discuss:** *What computer system in the video might raise ethical concerns for some people? What are those concerns?*\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-lightbulb-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Discussion Goal:** Guide students to recognize that artificial intelligence and robotics—particularly systems designed to collect personal data or replace human workers—can raise ethical concerns regarding privacy, job displacement, and the broader social impact of technology. Encourage them to explore how these concerns might differ among various stakeholders and emphasize the importance of transparency, responsible data handling, and dignity in AI-driven solutions."
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "6c84e17c-98ec-426c-bc2a-f9278891afe0",
        "lesson_activity.key": "fa8bfc3c-5061-469b-b5c7-2bd34e394fba"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "32f53228-86f7-4169-905f-a4ecb839e324",
      "position": 1,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:**  Put students into groups of three or four.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-file-text-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Distribute:** Give each group several blank half-sheets of paper and access to either the class FigJam or slides.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:**  Define *ethics*.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Assign each group a distinct role – there are four roles per scenario. Direct students to Lesson 12, Level 1 to review the scenario with their group.",
        "duration": "20",
        "name": "Role Playing",
        "progression_name": "AI and Emerging Technologies Ethics Roleplaying"
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "32f53228-86f7-4169-905f-a4ecb839e324",
        "lesson_activity.key": "b279dfe1-1b84-4771-9f95-59848fc4357a"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "a626e6f5-d021-42f3-ac73-5be5b77309a3",
      "position": 2,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Students should populate the digital sticky notes on the FigJam or slide that corresponds to the Scenario and Role that they are examining. There are a variety of different discussion questions that the students can choose to answer with their group.",
        "tips": [
          {
            "type": "teachingTip",
            "markdown": "The students' goal is to think and respond from the perspective of the role which they are assigned—considering their concerns, responsibilities, and priorities. As students think about their role’s perspective, they can use the information provided to consider:\n- What does this role value most in this situation?\n- What pressures or responsibilities influence my decisions?\n- How might I react to different arguments from other roles?\n- What personal experiences, beliefs, or priorities shape my viewpoint?\n\nEven if students don’t personally agree with the role’s stance, encourage them to try to think like their role and defend their position as convincingly as possible. The goal isn’t to win a debate—it’s to deeply understand different perspectives on ethics, privacy, and technology in education."
          }
        ]
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "a626e6f5-d021-42f3-ac73-5be5b77309a3",
        "lesson_activity.key": "b279dfe1-1b84-4771-9f95-59848fc4357a"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "bb65bec9-1253-411f-a69a-eba57f19a4a8",
      "position": 3,
      "properties": {
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "bb65bec9-1253-411f-a69a-eba57f19a4a8",
        "lesson_activity.key": "b279dfe1-1b84-4771-9f95-59848fc4357a"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "116f67dc-3050-494b-bcf1-86d0930c817c",
      "position": 4,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:**  Remind students that their proposal should reflect a compromise between roles, not just one perspective. Encourage students to justify their ideas and challenge each other’s assumptions respectfully.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Have groups present their proposals and discuss differences in approaches.",
        "tips": [
          {
            "type": "teachingTip",
            "markdown": "If groups struggle to agree, prompt them to identify common ground or adjust their proposal to better address concerns. Ask groups to consider whose interests are best served by their proposal and who might still have concerns."
          }
        ]
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "116f67dc-3050-494b-bcf1-86d0930c817c",
        "lesson_activity.key": "b279dfe1-1b84-4771-9f95-59848fc4357a"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "b207f3f0-76d3-4a83-8fda-64fa0518b214",
      "position": 5,
      "properties": {
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "b207f3f0-76d3-4a83-8fda-64fa0518b214",
        "lesson_activity.key": "b279dfe1-1b84-4771-9f95-59848fc4357a"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "d6026756-7bb3-44e7-9b4d-70b345c26f3b",
      "position": 6,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-comments\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Discuss:** *Share an insight or highlight from your group's roleplaying experience.*\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-lightbulb-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Discussion Goal:** The goal with this discussion is to allow students to share their learning and ethical explorations with the class, and to talk through their personal thoughts about the ethical considerations of the scenario apart from the role that had been assumed.",
        "tips": [
          {
            "type": "teachingTip",
            "markdown": "Student guidelines could address fairness, transparency, privacy, or another important ethical concern. Example: \"AI systems should be transparent about how they make decisions to ensure accountability.\""
          }
        ]
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "d6026756-7bb3-44e7-9b4d-70b345c26f3b",
        "lesson_activity.key": "b279dfe1-1b84-4771-9f95-59848fc4357a"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "93ef8e31-6c7c-44a0-a34c-0f6e1d6319bf",
      "position": 7,
      "properties": {
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "93ef8e31-6c7c-44a0-a34c-0f6e1d6319bf",
        "lesson_activity.key": "b279dfe1-1b84-4771-9f95-59848fc4357a"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "be362356-ad6e-4ca1-8b78-a1b72e4ca847",
      "position": 8,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Based on your discussion, students should identify a key ethical value or rule that should guide the responsible use of technology. They should write this on a half-sheet of paper.",
        "duration": "15",
        "name": "AI Guidelines"
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "be362356-ad6e-4ca1-8b78-a1b72e4ca847",
        "lesson_activity.key": "b279dfe1-1b84-4771-9f95-59848fc4357a"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "bea1ce52-2c41-451f-aa1f-7757b6342e8e",
      "position": 9,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Direct students to Lesson 12, Level 2. Students will work through one of the scenarios on Levels 2 and 3, following a similar pattern: they will review the scenario, roleplay one of the roles that are offered, reflect on their learning with the class, and write an ethical guideline about AI and emerging technologies that is synthesized from their discussions.",
        "progression_name": "Check for Understanding"
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "bea1ce52-2c41-451f-aa1f-7757b6342e8e",
        "lesson_activity.key": "b279dfe1-1b84-4771-9f95-59848fc4357a"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "a48f6ac5-7fa3-4cef-bc61-0826f810d744",
      "position": 10,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Have students hang up the ethical guidelines that they have developed around the classroom or in the hallway. They should wander around and read what other classmates have written as a result of their learning and conversations.",
        "progression_name": "Student Survey",
        "tips": [
          {
            "type": "teachingTip",
            "markdown": "You can have students vote for their top three ethical guidelines – by having them write a plus or star on the ethical guideline, or with the use of stickers. This can lead to an interesting conversation in which the top three guidelines are reviewed and discussed as a class."
          }
        ]
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "a48f6ac5-7fa3-4cef-bc61-0826f810d744",
        "lesson_activity.key": "b279dfe1-1b84-4771-9f95-59848fc4357a"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "7fd92a00-75f7-4a9c-b282-e90e35734132",
      "position": 1,
      "properties": {
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "7fd92a00-75f7-4a9c-b282-e90e35734132",
        "lesson_activity.key": "191453c9-3b4b-45d8-8329-3edcb65b8add"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "2e0c6754-ca45-411e-aeee-50461a3f09e2",
      "position": 2,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Review the lesson objectives.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Review the Question of the Day.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-comments\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Discuss:** Click through the animated slide to display the prompts.\n- *Which guideline do you personally believe is the most important?*\n- *If only one could be universally adopted, which would you choose and why?*\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-lightbulb-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Discussion Goal:** Allow students to synthesize their learning for the day and to advocate for their own personal ethical points of view as a capstone activity."
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "2e0c6754-ca45-411e-aeee-50461a3f09e2",
        "lesson_activity.key": "191453c9-3b4b-45d8-8329-3edcb65b8add"
      }
    },
